  <brief_summary>
    <textblock>
      The purpose of this study is to compare two techniques for treating patients with Whiplash
      Associated Disorders, in relation to: disability, balance, cervical pain and cervical range
      of motion.

      The hypothesis: The APOS kit treatment is more effective than the short wave therapy.
    </textblock>
  </brief_summary>
